ENUGU – The National Executive Committee (NEC) of Ohanaeze Ndigbo World­wide has passed a vote of confidence on its President General, Ambassador Pro­fessor George Obiozor. The motion for the vote of confidence was moved by the National Publicity Secretary of the association, Chiedozie Alex Ogbonnia. Ogbonnia, in a statement made available to journal­ists in Enugu on Saturday, expressed immense delight that Professor Obiozor had shown leadership in the quest for a Nigerian pres­ident to emerge from the South East of Nigeria. Wife Reportedly Stabs Husband’s Nephew Over Broken Mirror Analysing The Retaining, Removal Of Nigeria’s Oil Subsidy Ogbonnia explained that Obiozor had maintained an unwavering and vigorous advocacy for the prevalent Igbo project. “Obiozor has used his pro­found intellectual prowess, diplomatic finesse, national and foreign contacts to sus­tain the Igbo dream,” he said Ogbonnia recalled the Obiozor deliberations with the Southern and Middle Belt Leadership Forum led by Chief Edwin Clarke that gave rise to a communique that it would be a regretta­ble requiem for any political party that failed to pick its presidential candidate from the South. The Forum asserted that Nigeria was founded on a negotiated unity between the diverse Nigerian na­tionalities and that only a balance of interests among the component units could guarantee its corporate ex­istence.